No&euml;l Le Gra&euml;t (FFF President): &ldquo;For me, Benzema is a very good player. I have never criticised his qualities. On the contrary, he is proving again this year at Real Madrid that he is one of the best players in his position. But the adventure with France is over.&rdquo; [RMC]<br />
<br />
Benzema: &ldquo;No&euml;l I thought you were not interfering in the decisions of the coach! Know that it is I and I alone that can put an end to my international career. If you think I'm finished, let me play for one of the countries for which I'm eligible and we'll see...&rdquo;

Florentino Perez: &ldquo;In recent years we've experienced one of the best periods in our club's history. Our football team has added to Real Madrid's legacy by lifting 4 European Cups in 5 years &amp; 17 trophies in 9 seasons &amp; we continue to top the UEFA ranking for a 6th straight year.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Florentino Perez: &ldquo;Everything we stand for &amp; that we've achieved together throughout our 117-year history is based on the strength &amp; support of our members, who alongside the millions of fans located across all of the continents have been &amp; continue to be our biggest asset.&rdquo;

Hazard: &quot;After having played with Benzema for three or fourth months, I think that, right now, he's the best striker in the world.&rdquo; [marca]<br />
<br />
Hazard: &quot;But [also] away from Benzema&rsquo;s role as a striker, he makes others better.&quot;

